50|$|Pumsavana is a <b>rite</b> <b>of</b> passage {{observed}} {{when the}} pregnancy begins to show, typically in {{or after the}} third month of pregnancy and usually before the fetus starts moving in the womb. The ceremony celebrates the <b>rite</b> <b>of</b> passage of the developing fetus, marking the stage where the baby begins to kick as a milestone in a baby's development.|$|R
